Bunch of code that use nodemcu board.

https://www.nodemcu.com


Driver for Arduino IDE 

    follow https://github.com/esp8266/Arduino or https://arduino-esp8266.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installing.html

    you have to add this as as new platform.

    no extra library needs to be installed. all comes with this. try examples now.

    On Sketch IDE use ESP8266 12E and 9600 upload speed.

other docs

    https://randomnerdtutorials.com/how-to-install-esp8266-board-arduino-ide/

    https://github.com/arduino/Arduino/wiki/Unofficial-list-of-3rd-party-boards-support-urls

    Driver for com port https://sparks.gogo.co.nz/ch340.html

    wifi examples: https://arduino-esp8266.readthedocs.io/en/latest/esp8266wifi/readme.html



